---
import SimplePageLayout from '../../layouts/SimplePageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../data/site';

const schemas = [
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: `${SITE.url}/` },
      {
        '@type': 'ListItem',
        position: 2,
        name: 'Responsible Disclosure',
        item: `${SITE.url}/responsible-disclosure/`,
      },
    ],
  },
];
---

<SimplePageLayout
  title="Responsible Disclosure Policy | imizicyber"
  description="imizicyber's responsible disclosure policy for reporting security vulnerabilities. How to contact us, what to expect, and our commitment to researchers."
  canonicalUrl={`${SITE.url}/responsible-disclosure/`}
  ogTitle="Responsible Disclosure Policy | imizicyber"
  ogDescription="How to report security vulnerabilities to imizicyber. Our responsible disclosure policy and commitment to the security research community."
  twitterTitle="Responsible Disclosure Policy | imizicyber"
  twitterDescription="How to report security vulnerabilities to imizicyber. Our responsible disclosure policy, scope, and commitment to the security research community."
  schemas={schemas}
>
  <article class="policy-article">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Responsible Disclosure' }]} />
    <h1>Responsible Disclosure Policy</h1>
    <p>
      At imizicyber, we take security seriously -- not only for our clients, but for our own systems
      as well. We welcome and appreciate security researchers who take the time to report
      vulnerabilities responsibly.
    </p>

    <h2>Scope</h2>
    <p>
      This policy applies to the following assets owned and operated by IMIZI Cyber Consulting Ltd:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>imizicyber.com</code> and all subdomains</li>
      <li>Any publicly accessible services or APIs operated by imizicyber</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to report a vulnerability</h2>
    <p>
      Please send your report to <strong>security@imizicyber.com</strong>. We strongly encourage you
      to encrypt your report using our <a href="/.well-known/pgp-key.asc">PGP public key</a>.
    </p>
    <p>Your report should include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A clear description of the vulnerability</li>
      <li>Steps to reproduce the issue</li>
      <li>The potential impact of the vulnerability</li>
      <li>Any proof-of-concept code, screenshots, or logs (if applicable)</li>
      <li>Your contact information for follow-up</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What to expect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Acknowledgement:</strong> We will acknowledge receipt of your report within 48 hours
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Triage:</strong> We will assess the report and provide an initial severity rating within
        5 business days
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Updates:</strong> We will keep you informed of our progress towards remediation
      </li>
      <li><strong>Resolution:</strong> We will notify you when the vulnerability has been fixed</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our commitments</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We will not take legal action against researchers who follow this policy</li>
      <li>We will work with you to understand and resolve the issue</li>
      <li>We will credit you (if desired) when we disclose the vulnerability</li>
      <li>We will respond to your report in a timely manner</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Rules of engagement</h2>
    <p>We ask that you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Do not access, modify, or delete data that does not belong to you</li>
      <li>Do not perform denial-of-service attacks</li>
      <li>Do not perform social engineering attacks against our staff</li>
      <li>
        Do not publicly disclose the vulnerability until we have had a reasonable opportunity to
        remediate
      </li>
      <li>Make a good-faith effort to avoid privacy violations and disruption to our services</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Contact:</strong> security@imizicyber.com<br />
      <strong>PGP Key:</strong>
      <a href="/.well-known/pgp-key.asc">/.well-known/pgp-key.asc</a><br />
      <strong>security.txt:</strong>
      <a href="/.well-known/security.txt">/.well-known/security.txt</a>
    </div>

    <p>Thank you for helping us keep our systems and our clients secure.</p>
  </article>
</SimplePageLayout>

<style>
  .policy-article {
    padding: 100px 0 60px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.5vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 32px 0 10px;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
  }
  p {
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    color: var(--txt);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  ul {
    margin: 0 0 14px 24px;
    color: var(--txt);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--acc);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: var(--bg2);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--acc);
  }
</style>
